y support, it might be allowed, but for past issues with native image runs, I shouldn’t add it. I need to research the documentation carefully to ensure everything is properly set up.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No deterministic setup is required for com.sksamuel.hoplite:hoplite-core:3.0.0.RC1. The resolved artifact depends only on Kotlin stdlib/reflect and kotlinx-coroutines, and the core jar includes in-memory/property-based sources, default decoders, default mappers, and the built-in Java properties parser, so meaningful coverage is reachable without Docker, extra Maven modules, or required environment/system properties.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Hoplite documentation commonly demonstrates YAML/JSON/HOCON/TOML config files, but those formats require separate hoplite-* modules. For hoplite-core-only coverage, tests should use MapPropertySource, PropsPropertySource, .properties resources, or core APIs rather than assuming YAML/JSON parsing is available.\",\n    \"Hoplite 3 changes default environment-variable behavior: EnvironmentVariablesPropertySource is now part of the default sources and can read process environment. Tests that use ConfigLoaderBuilder.default() should avoid depending on ambient CI environment values; prefer explicit/in-memory sources for deterministic assertions.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_08e747d6dfc4b6e6016a40aa2b73208190ab869134775564fe\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2126, "output": 1185, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37103, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782622750593, "responseId": "resp_08e747d6dfc4b6e6016a40aa1f156481908a84473fa3887edc"}}
